title: Artemis 1 launch boosts ESA’s exploration ambitions
summary: The successful launch of the Artemis 1 mission comes just in time for the European Space Agency as it seeks support from its member states for new exploration initiatives.

title: Space Force opens door to Blue Origin with new cooperative agreement
summary: The U.S. Space Systems Command signed an agreement with Blue Origin that “paves the way” for the company’s New Glenn rocket to compete for national security launch contracts

title: SpaceX ship headed 1000 kilometers out to sea for expendable Falcon 9 launch
summary: A SpaceX recovery ship is headed more than a thousand kilometers downrange to support the second expendable Falcon 9 rocket launch in...

title: Orion capsule closes in for lunar flyby
summary: Nearly five days after its sky-lighting launch, NASA’s unpiloted Orion crew capsule closed in on the moon Sunday, on course for a critical rocket firing and lunar flyby Monday to whip the craft into a distant orbit. The goal is to pave the way toward a piloted flight around the moon in 2024.

title: SpaceX to launch last new cargo Dragon spacecraft
summary: A SpaceX Dragon launching soon to the International Space Station is the last cargo version of the spacecraft the company expects to build, with one more crewed spacecraft under construction.

title: Orion ready for lunar flyby maneuver
summary: NASA has approved plans to proceed with the next critical milestone in the Artemis 1 mission, a maneuver by the uncrewed Orion spacecraft as it flies by the moon Nov. 21.

title: White House, Congress praise long-delayed first SLS launch
summary: The inaugural flight of the Space Launch System won positive reactions from the White House and Congress, celebrating the successful liftoff while overlooking the vehicle’s extensive delays.

title: NASA Awards Extension for Space, Earth Science Data Analysis Contract
summary: NASA has awarded a six-month extension to ADNET Systems Inc. of Bethesda, Maryland, for the Space and Earth Science Data Analysis (SESDA IV) contract.

title: AST SpaceMobile searching for funds to accelerate constellation
summary: A year and a half after netting around $417 million through its IPO, AST SpaceMobile is seeking more funds to accelerate a direct-to-smartphone constellation that has fallen behind a key regulatory deadline.

title: NASA Awards Contract for Liquid Helium Acquisition at Kennedy
summary: NASA has selected Air Products and Chemicals, Inc of Allentown, Pennsylvania, to supply 33 million liters of liquid helium to the agency’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida.
